description: NrdcSnTerminationUeCfg: Configuration table specifying whether SN termination is allowed for UEs on specific cells, including timestamps, location, cell identifiers, and configuration details.  dateTime: Timestamp of the configuration; Area_Name: Geographic area of the cell; CellId: Unique identifier of the cell; Id2: Redundant cell identifier; Id3: SN Termination configuration type; Id4: Configuration type identifier; vsDataType: Data type identifier; vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format; NrdcSnTerminationUeCfg.nrdcSnTerminationUeCfgId: Configuration ID; NrdcSnTerminationUeCfg.nrdcSnTermAllowed: Flag indicating whether SN termination is allowed (0=no, 1=yes).
